we can change the output of log command!
we can customize the output of the log command by:

git log --pretty=format:""          //in double quotes we specify format string!
                                    //it can be combination of plaintext and place holders


git log --pretty=format:"hello"         //just show hello for all commits

git log --pretty=format:"hello %an"     //after hello write author name

git log --pretty=format:"%an %H"        //author name + full commit hash

git log --pretty=format:"%an %h"        //author name + brief commit hash

git log --pretty=format:"%an %h"        //author name + brief commit hash

git log --pretty=format:"%an %h on %cd"        //author name + brief commit hash + date
                                               //cd stand for commit date

git log --pretty=format:"%Cgreen %an %h on %cd"     //all the line is green
                                                    //C stand for color

git log --pretty=format:"%Cgreen %an %Creset %h on %cd"     //just author name is green

git log --pretty=format:"%Cgreen %an %Cblue %h on %cd"      //author name is green
                                                            //rest of the line is blue!


Note: check git-log documentation (git-scm.com/docs/git-log)
      to see all these place holders list


